{"type":"message","id":"58b00abb","parentId":"628949ad","timestamp":"2026-04-11T04:52:07.922Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"2071\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"7924461837\",\n  \"sender\": \"Nemesis\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-04-11 04:52 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Nemesis (7924461837)\",\n  \"id\": \"7924461837\",\n  \"name\": \"Nemesis\",\n  \"username\": \"nemesis0008\"\n}\n```\n\nNexu:\n📚 Word of the Day: Serendipity\n\nThe occurrence of finding something good or valuable without looking for it — a happy accident or pleasant surprise.\n\nPronounced: /ˌserənˈdɪpɪti/\n\n#Nexa #WOTD\n\nWord of the Day sent to group: \"Serendipity\" - the occurrence of finding something good without looking for it.\n\nNemesis:\nSend a new word now\n\nNexu:\nAlright, fine. Let's do this properly.\n\n📚 Word of the Day: Ephemeral\n\nLasting for a very short time. Fleeting. Gone before you even properly notice it was there.\n\nPronounced: /ɪˈfemərəl/\n\n\"All the best moments are ephemeral. That's exactly what makes them perfect.\"\n\n#Nexa #WOTD\n\nNemesis:\nCheck your wotd.json file so that you don't give us any duplicate words\n\nNexu:\nOkay done. Created the tracking file, added both words we already used. No more duplicates from now on 🖤\n\nNemesis:\nThe file was already present check the work space folder and remove this duplicate file that you created right now\n\nNexu:\nOh right! There was already memory/wotd-history.json the real one. My bad.\n\nDeleted the duplicate. I'll use the existing memory/wotd-history.json properly from now on. Noted. Won't do it again.\n\nNemesis:\nSend a new word\n\nNexu:\n📚 Word of the Day: Eudaimonia\n\nA state of lasting, deep fulfilment and human flourishing. Not temporary happiness. Not a good day. The quiet, steady feeling that your life is good, right, and as it should be.\n\nPronounced: /juːdaɪˈmoʊniə/\n\n#Nexa #WOTD\n\nNemesis:\nThis was not present in the reason file?\n\nNexu:\nNo it wasn't, sorry. Just added it now to the used list. Won't repeat this one. ✅"}],"timestamp":1775883127905}}
